          <section eId="sec_43-99-010">
            <num>43.99.010</num>
            <heading>Accounts to be kept by persons subject to tax.</heading>
            <content>
              <p>Sec. 43.99.010.   Accounts to be kept by persons subject to tax.
A person subject to a tax shall keep in permanent form at the person's principal place of business or occupation within the state correct accounts in a manner that will readily disclose, upon examination, the amount of tax due the state.  The department may adopt regulations for the making and keeping of these records.</p>
            </content>
          </section>
          <section eId="sec_43-99-950">
            <num>43.99.950</num>
            <heading>Definitions.</heading>
            <content>
              <p>Sec. 43.99.950.   Definitions.
Except in
AS 43.70
, in this title,
(1) commissioner means the commissioner of revenue; and
(2) department means the Department of Revenue.</p>
            </content>
          </section>
